text: there is persistent nonenhancement of the left vertebral artery over a long segment from the proximal portion to the level of v3.only a short segment close to the origin is seen to enhance.previously noted small focus of slight enhancement, in the mid left vertebral artery is not seen on the present study.there is mild decrease in the size of the left vertebral artery in the v3 segment compared to the prior study and is unclear if this is due to better spatial resolution/mild decrease in caliber.there is narrowing of the left v4 segment with mild decrease in size compared to the prior study.the left distal vertebral artery measures 2 mm, compared to the prior of 2.5 mm, appearing narrower distally.the origins of the arch vessels are patent.a small focus of calcification is noted at the brachiocephalic artery.the right common carotid and the right vertebral arteries are patent.the left common carotid artery is patent.the internal carotid arteries are patent without focal flow-limiting stenosis, occlusion or obvious aneurysm.circle of ___ and the intracranial arteries are incompletely imaged on the present study.there is small amount of fluid/mucosal thickening and aerosolized secretions in the sphenoid sinus and in the ethmoid air cells.there is redemonstration of the previously noted fractures, in the left c6 facet and adjacent to the transverse foramen, better evaluated on the prior c-spine study.a few small scattered nodes are noted.the thyroid is unremarkable.a few small scattered nodes are noted in both sides of the neck, some of which are borderline in size.evaluation at the level of maxilla and mandible is limited due to dental artifacts.
summary: persistent lack of enhancement of the left vertebral artery over a long segment, mild decrease in the size of the distal left vertebral artery, in the v3 and v4 segments compared to the prior study.only a short segment close to the origin is patent proximally.follow up as clinically indicated to assess for stability/progression.fractures noted involving the left c6 facet and transverse foramen, better evaluated on prior ct c spine study.other details as above.fluid and mucosal thickening with aerosolized secretions in the sphenoid sinus.

text: there are bilateral pleural effusions and bibasilar atelectases.there is minimal soft tissue density material surrounding the left internal carotid artery.it extends to the subcutaneous tissues anterior to the left sternocleidomastoid muscle.there is no evidence of contrast extravasation.the parotid glands are unremarkable.there are tiny lymph nodes within the neck.the visualized portions of the brain are unremarkable.the bones are normal.

text: ct of the neck: there is an extensive partially solid, partially rim-enhancing, likely an infectious, phlegmonous process extending from the left inferior palatine tonsil (series 7, image 29) caudally to the level of the true vocal cord (series 7, image 51), and centered in the left lingual tonsil (series 7, image 37).sagittal images nicely show the craniocaudal extent of this process (series 801b, image 45).there is narrowing of the airway at the level of the lingual tonsil (series 7, image 37) and at the level of the hyoid bone (series 7, image 43).there is extensive retropharyngeal edema with effacement of the (left greater than right) pyriform sinus and edema of the false vocal cord on the left side.the same swelling and hypodensity extends to involve the epiglottis and left aryepiglottic fold.there are no pathologically enlarged lymph nodes; however, enhancing level 2a lymph nodes are seen on the left which measure about 7 mm (series 7, image 39 and series 7, image 32) with possible central necrosis.overall, etiology of this process is most likely infectious given acute onset and widespread craniocaudal dimension, malignancy is unlikely, but cannot be completely excluded especially since the process is centered in the lingual tonsil.the jugular veins, vertebral and carotid arteries are normal.the thyroid gland are normal.the lung apices are clear.the paranasal sinuses and mastoid air cells are clear.
summary: rim-enhancing likely infectious phlegmonous process extending from the lower part of the left palatine tonsil to the true vocal cord, and centered in left lingual tonsil.moderate to severe narrowing of the airway at lingual tonsil level and at the level of the hyoid bone.no foreign bodies.extensive retropharyngeal edema effacing the left pyriform sinus and extending to the level of the true vocal cords.two 7 mm enhancing left level ia cervical lymph nodes.mediastinum is currently not involved, but concern for further caudal progression remains.

text: there is no supraclavicular nor right neck lymphadenopathy.there are several small nonenlarged lymph nodes, which are nonpathologic.at the periphery of the image, there is a large shoulder mass.for further discussion of this finding, please refer to shoulder ct of ___.there are no masses within the superficial soft tissues of the neck.there are no enhancement abnormalities.there is asymmetry noted of the pharynx.specifically, there is increased soft tissue fullness at the area of the left palatine tonsils and vallecular recess.this has an asymmetric appearance.direct visualization is recommended.there are no bony changes identified within the mandible.incidental note is made of multiple nonenlarged mediastinal lymph nodes.there is also scarring within the lung apices.correlation could be obtained with chest ct if warranted.
summary: no evidence of right-sided supraclavicular or neck adenopathy.right shoulder lesion is better evaluated on the shoulder ct of ___.asymmetric soft tissue fullness to the left palatine tonsil region.direct visualization is recommended to exclude mass.

text: subcutaneous air is seen extensively through the left anterior neck, dissecting deep to the platysma and surrounding multiple structures including the left submandibular gland, left strap muscle, left sternocleidomastoid, and as deep as the left subclavian artery from its origin from the aortic arch.small amount of air is also seen tracking along the right anterior neck.an apical pneumothorax is identified.though they are calcifications in the carotid arteries and the aortic arch, there is no evidence of vascular injury.no fractures are identified, though there are extensive degenerative changes of the cervical spine.

text: there is complete occlusion of the left common carotid artery from the level of the thoracic inlet to the carotid bulb.this occlusion extends into the internal carotid artery up to the level of the cavernous carotid with contrast seen distally in the left supraclinoid carotid and mca likely from collateral circulation from the circle of ___.also noted is an eccentric thrombus in the external carotid artery extending to the level of the angle of the mandible.this occlusion is felt to be secondary to a dissection given the mechanism of injury.also noted is irregularity along the walls of the common carotid just inferior to the carotid bulb on the right, which likely represents a small area of dissection in the right common carotid.no areas of active extravasation are noted.high-density contrast in the superior mediastinum (2:22) and in the apex of the lung (2:65) persists on the delayed phase images and appears to have fluid levels and is felt to be likely represent pooling contrast within venous branches.for instance, the inferior high contrast area appears to be in the azygos vein.no evidence of active extravasation is noted.there is right upper lobe atelectasis with endobronchial debris in the right upper lobe bronchus.a small amount of air is noted in the superior mediastinum.significant subcutaneous emphysema is noted in the anterior neck and chest wall extending into the posterior neck and retropharyngeal space.as mentioned on the concurrent c-spine ct, this is felt to arise from the trachea at the level of the thyroid cartilage.again noted are fractures of both posterior pedicles of c2 vertebral body without distraction of the dens.displaced fractures of the left hyoid greater cornu and the left lamina of the thyroid cartilage are noted.
summary: occlusion of the left common carotid and the left internal carotid artery extending up to the level of the cavernous carotid on the left with good flow from collaterals from the circle of ___ seen in the supraclinoid carotid and left mca is felt to be secondary to a dissection given mechanism of injury.thrombosis left external carotid artery.irregularity in the wall of the right common carotid artery just inferior to the carotid bulb is likely secondary to a small dissection.c-spine fractures as detailed on the cervical spine ct.left hyoid bone inferiorly displaced fracture of the greater cornu.left thyroid cartilage mildly displaced fracture.significant subcutaneous emphysema in the anterior neck is felt to be secondary to a tracheal injury at the level of the thyroid cartilage.these findings including the change from the wet read were discussed extensively with the thoracic surgery fellow, ___ ___, ___ ___ from the trauma surgery service, and dr.___ from ent via telephone at the time of initial review and then again at 8:45 a.m.final attending comment: there is mild short segment narrowing of the left vertebral artery just inferior to the c2 fracture and there is a small filling defect in the left vertebral artery at the level of the fracture.these findings likely represent intimal injury.

text: the patient is status post radiation therapy for carcinoma of the larynx.the previously noted left subglottic soft tissue mass is not well visualized on the current study.there is diffuse soft tissue fullness within the glottic soft tissues and in supraglottic region.the epiglottis is markedly thickened.additionally, there is a defect within the anterior larynx, an air is noted to traverse the anterior commissure and enter the deep soft tissue layer anteriorly.also noted is stranding of the subcutaneous fat, which could be related to post radiation change.there are small bilateral lymph nodes noted along the jugular chain, which do not meet ct criteria for pathologic enlargement.the thyroid and the remaining visualized soft tissues are within normal limits.the visualized osseous are grossly unremarkable.the visualized lung apices reveal extensive bullous change bilaterally.
summary: the patient is status post radiation therapy, and there is diffuse soft tissue fullness in the glottis and supraglottic region, as well as epiglottic thickening.there is also defect noted in the anterior larynx, with air through the anterior commissure, most likely representing necrosis of tissue that is related to radiation therapy, as discussed with dr.___.

text: again demonstrated are pooled secretions within the hypopharynx secondary to endotracheal intubation.an open surgical wound is noted anterior to the left sternocleidomastoid muscle.air is noted posterior to the trachea most likely within the esophagus.within the c4 corpectomy defect there is a suggestion of hypoattenuation with rim enhancement.the fat planes within the lateral neck are preserved.there is shotty lymphadenopathy throughout the anterior cervical chain.

text: multiple enlarged lymph nodes are noted in both sides of the neck, the largest measuring 1.7cm in the long axis in the iia zone on the right side.there is also an enlarged right retropharyngeal lymph node measures 1.3 x 1.0 cm with no significant change compared to ___ mri.the vessels and the carotid spaces are normal.the fat planes and the muscles in the neck are unremarkable.there is no narrowing of the ___-, oro- or hypo-pharynx.the thyroid appears unremarkable.the visualized portions of the posterior fossa structures are unremarkable.the visualized portions of the lung apices are clear.no osseous lytic or sclerotic lesions are noted.

text: there is complete occlusion of the left internal carotid artery at its origin with reconstitution at the level of the ophthalmic artery in the supraclinoid region.there is ectasia of the distal right common carotid artery and proximal internal carotid artery consistent with endarterectomy, clinical correlation advised.there is some irregularity of the common carotid artery below the level of this ectasia, probably representing some atherosclerotic narrowing.a metallic density is visualized in the region of this artery somewhat more inferiorly.the left vertebral artery is patent with a mild stenosis at its origin.there may also be some stenosis of the origin of the left subclavian artery and once again clinical correlation is advised.the right vertebral artery is diminutive and intermittently occluded in the neck.it does appear to be continuous with the proximal basilar artery.there is some irregularity and possible mild stenosis of the origin of the right subclavian artery.intracranially, there is no evidence of aneurysm.both middle cerebral artery groups are well visualized.the basilar artery is patent.there is considerable irregularity of the aortic arch, consistent with atherosclerotic plaque.
summary: occluded left internal carotid artery.appearance of the right carotid artery consistent with endarterectomy with some mild narrowing proximal to the ectasia.possible stenosis origin of the left vertebral artery and left subclavian artery.diminutive and intermittently occluded right vertebral artery.

text: there is no marker to indicate the level of palpable node.there are scattered cervical lymph nodes bilaterally, symmetric, and not enlarged or excessively numerous.the heterogeneous soft tissue density mass in the right maxillary sinus, causing expansion and destruction of the maxillary sinus walls, is stable compared to the ___ mri, allowing for differences in technique.there is a right periorbital subcutaneous soft tissue density which is enlarged from the mri obtained ___ (10 mm thick compared to 2.5 mm thick), image 2:8.there is bilateral subcutaneous edema at the level of the mandible, right greater than left.there is a right vallecular soft tissue density measuring 8.4 mm(ap) x 11.8 mm(trv).the parotid, submandibular, and thyroid glands are unremarkable in appearance.there is calcification of the bilateral internal carotid arteries at their origins and in their cavernous/supraclinoid segments.the left lung apical ground-glass opacity noted on the ___ ct torso, abutting the major fissure, is more solid in appearance and larger, measuring 1.3 cm x 0.6 cm.given its dependent position in the upper lobe, atelectasis could be considered, but tumor progression cannot be excluded.

text: asymmetry of the thyroid gland is seen, with an enlarged left thyroid lobe or nodule.in comparison to the ___ spect ct examination, there is marked enlargement of this lobe with obscuration of the neighboring ___ planes against the strap muscles and adjacent internal jugular vein.hyperdense material seen tracking along these ___ planes superiorly and inferiorly.at the level of hyoid, there is now slight rightward deviation of the trachea (2:47), with slightly hyperdense material (hounsfield units approximately 40), representing blood products.there is neighboring stranding anteriorly, just inferior to the mandible (2:53).there is obliteration of the left piriform sinus (2:57) secondary to neighboring mass effect.the tracheal compression is detected.included views of the lung apices are clear.

text: ct angiography of the neck demonstrates occlusion of the left internal carotid artery as seen on the previous cta examination.since the previous study, there has been carotid endarterectomy on the right side with widely patent carotid artery on that side.there are soft tissue changes adjacent to the carotid artery near the bifurcation and distally which are new since the prior study and are likely related to the recent procedure.there is a small amount of soft tissue changes and air within the soft tissues, also related to the recent surgery.there continues to be stenosis of the right vertebral artery in the distal cervical region with nonvisualization of the distal right vertebral artery.the left vertebral artery remains unchanged and patent in appearance.

text: extensive soft tissue swelling throughout the superficial and deep spaces of the left neck and abnormal thickening and enhancement of the left sternocleidomastoid and posterior cervical muscles are again seen (2:29).there is increased rim thickening and enhancement of an organizing fluid collection along the left neck extending posteriorly (2:33) since ___, with a dominant collection measuring 34 x 7 mm (2:28).previously noted drains have been removed with subcutaneous gas likely reflecting packing material within a lateral incision (2:54).no bony erosions are detected.there is improved retropharyngeal swelling with decreased mass effect on the neighboring airway, including slight restoration of the left piriform sinus and decreased swelling of the left aryepiglottic fold and epiglottis.the airway remains patent.no new fluid collections are seen.there is no subcutaneous emphysema.neighboring great vessels remain patent, although there is continued marked narrowing of the left internal jugular vein (2:34) as it passes through the area of inflammation in the left neck.included views of the lung apices demonstrates minimal paraseptal emphysema (301b:68).the thyroid is normal.
summary: organizing rim-enhancing fluid collection concerning for an abscess tracking along the left lateral and posterior neck, overall slightly worsened since ___, with increased size of a dominant posterior collection measuring up to 8 mm, and increased thickeness of an enhancing rind.improved retropharyngeal swelling with decreased mass effect on the neighboring airway, including slight restoration of the left piriform sinus and decreased swelling of the left aryepiglottic fold and epiglottis.removal of surgical drains with subcutaneous gas in the left neck possibly reflecting packing material within the surgical incision.continued severe focal narrowing the left internal jugular vein as it courses through the area of inflammation in the left neck.

text: soft tissues of the anterior neck are unremarkable, without stranding or skin thickening.there is no focal fluid collection or abscess.palatine tonsils and adenoids are unremarkable.the retropharyngeal soft tissues are unremarkable.imaged portions of the ethmoid and maxillary sinuses are normal.the imaged portion of the brain is better assessed on dedicated brain ct imaging.the imaged portion of the lungs and chest are better assessed on accompanying chest ct.oropharynx is otherwise unremarkable.the osseous structures demonstrate no focal lytic or sclerotic lesion.

text: again there is evidence of occlusion of the right common carotid artery, partial collateral flow is again identified in the right external carotid artery, the superior thyroid artery as well as the lingual and facial arteries appears patent.apparently the ascending pharyngeal artery as well as the maxillary artery are also patent.there is persistent reconstitution of the supraclinoid segment, presumably from collateral flow.on the left cervical carotid bifurcation, again approximately 50% of carotid stenosis is identified involving the left internal carotid artery with soft plaque formation.significant tortuosity and kinking is again noted in the mid- to- distal cervical carotid artery on the left.the right vertebral artery is patent and the left vertebral artery is slightly smaller arising directly from the aortic arch with mild stenosis at its origin.persistent mural atherosclerotic plaquing in the aortic arch and brachiocephalic artery.small filling defects are again demonstrated on the left posterior cerebral artery.unchanged mucus retention cyst on the right maxillary sinus and multilevel degenerative changes in the cervical spine.

text: there is marked soft tissue swelling and phlegmonous material/enlarged lymphnodes surrounding the right body, angle, and ramus of the mandible (2:36-68).the phlegmonous region measures approximately 8.3 x 4.4 x 6.9 cm.there is no discrete drainable fluid collection.the right submandibular gland is slightly displaced posteriorly.there is mild compression of the airways with leftward displacement of the oropharynx/larynx (2:55).a defect is seen in the cortex along the inner margin of the mandibular body (2:58) along with a tiny adjacent focus of air, likely the point of entry of the infectious/inflammatory process from the adjacent reported cavity of tooth #20.prominent lymph nodes are seen along the right neck, measuring up to 11 mm (2:61), likely reactive in nature.the thyroid gland is unremarkable.aside from mild apical pleural parenchymal scarring, the visualized portions of the lungs are unremarkable.this study was not optimized for visualization of the intracranial contents.limited views of the brain are unremarkable.bilateral mucus retention cysts or mucosal thickening is seen within the maxillary sinuses.the remainder of the visualized portions of the paranasal sinuses and mastoid air cells are well aerated.
summary: extensive soft tissue stranding and phlegmonous material/enlarged lymphnodes surrounding the right mandible, as described above.there is an associated defect in the medial cortex of the right body of the mandible, adjacent to the reported tooth #20 dental caries, likely representing the psuedopassage of infectious/inflammatory material.mild leftward displacement of the airway by the adjacent inflammatory/infectious phlegmonous region without present obstruction of the airway.

text: a central line is present within the right internal jugular vein.there is no associated hematoma.the nasopharynx and oropharynx are normal.the salivary glands are unremarkable.the thyroid is symmetric and homogeneous.small, nonpathologically enlarged cervical chain lymph nodes are identified.

text: streak artifact from metallic fillings limits evaluation of adjacent soft tissue structures.there is prominence of the supraglottic anterior soft tissue structures.the visualized portions of the airway are widely patent.there is soft tissue density in the left nasal sinus.there is slight mucosal thickening of the right maxillary sinus.the thyroid and major vessels of the neck appear normal.the visualized portions of the brain are unremarkable.osseous structures are unremarkable.the visualized portions of the lung apices appear normal.

text: since the study of one day earlier, there continues to be strand- like density in the soft tissues from the level of the right temporal region, extending inferiorly through the right anterior neck, and more caudally into the right anterior chest wall, and the mediastinum.a previously identified right pleural effusion at the apex is smaller.no neck abscess is seen.

text: the right internal carotid artery is medialized.there continues to be thrombus extending from the distal-most right common carotid artery into the carotid bulb and further, into the bifurcation, with thrombus extending into the internal carotid artery.however, the thrombus burden has markedly diminished from the prior examination, when the thrombus filled the lumen of both the proximal internal and external carotid arteries.thrombus now extends approximately 19 mm from the common carotid into the proximal internal carotid artery.most of the lumen is now patent, as is much of the external carotid artery lumen.there is a small amount of thrombus remaining within the external carotid artery and the superior thyroidal artery origin.the distal right internal carotid artery measures 4.5 mm and the distal left internal carotid artery measures 6.5 mm.the previously seen right middle cerebral artery thrombus is not evaulated on the current neck cta as the superior division of the middle cerebral artery is not fully included in the imaging field-of-view.there is no other evidence of thrombus in the remaining neck vessels.there is marked atherosclerotic calcification of the aortic arch and the origins of the great vessels.there is a three-vessel aortic arch, and the origins of the bilateral vertebral arteries are patent.the vertebral arteries are tortuous in their course.the thyroid gland is enlarged and multinodular.there are patchy ground-glass airspace opacities in both lung apices, as well as bilateral pleural effusions, partially visualized.there are degenerative changes of the cervical spine, most advanced at c5-c6.a nasogastric tube is in place.
summary: marked interval reduction in the "burden" of thrombus in the distal right common carotid artery with extension into that proximal internal and external carotid artery.there is now flow, with opacfication, distal to the site of the thrombus.partially-visualized bilateral pleural effusions and pulmonary edema, compatible with chf, increased from prior.

text: no abscesses, enlarged lymph nodes, or masses in the region of the recurrent laryngeal nerves are noted.the partially imaged chest is best evaluated on the concurrent chest ct.the visible vessels are patent except for the right distal vertebral artery which appears to be chronically occluded, mildly progressed compared to ___.partially imaged brain is unremarkable.the visible paranasal sinuses and mastoid air cells are well aerated.
summary: mild degenerative change of the cervical spine.likely chronic occlusion of the distal right vertebral artery.no mass or other acute findings seen in the neck.

text: the origins of the common carotid and vertebral arteries are patent without significant stenosis.the bilateral common, internal, and external carotid arteries are normal in appearance.there is no evidence of hemodynamically significant stenosis or dissection.minimal luminal diameters of the proximal and distal cervical ica segments are 6.6 or 4.1 on the right side and 6.4 or 4.1 mm on the left.the cervical portions of the vertebral arteries likewise demonstrate normal contrast opacification.the visualized portions of the intracranial vasculature are likewise unremarkable.incidental note is made of prominent cervical lymph nodes bilaterally.multiple patchy pulmonary nodules may represent small foci of aspiration but are better characterized in the ct torso.

text: a large mass centered in the right base of tongue measures 3.2 x 3.1 x 2.9 cm (cc x trv x ap).posteriorly, the mass crosses midline and effaces the valleculae, right more than left.anteriorly, there is near-complete loss of the fat plane between the mass and the posterior border of the hyoid bone.while there is invasion of the superior preglottic fat, there is no evidence of extension into the glottis, itself.an enlarged right level iia lymph node demonstrates abnormal enhancement, mild adjacent fat-stranding, and loss of fatty hilum.a 10 mm lymph node within the inferior aspect of the superficial right parotid gland is mildly prominent, but maintains its fatty hilum.right level va and vb lymph nodes are moderately prominent in size and number as well.the largest left-sided lymph node is a level ii node, 16 mm in greatest diameter, which has somewhat abnormal configuration with some loss of its fatty hilum.the examination is otherwise significant for moderate degenerative changes of the cervical spine.
summary: large right base of tongue mass, 3.2 cm in greatest diameter, crossing midline, posteriorly.likely metastatic right level iia lymph node.moderately enlarged but numerous right level va and vb nodes are also highly suspicious for neoplastic involvement.

text: there is a large multiloculated rim enhancing fluid collection with numberous locules of gas centered within the left mucosal pharyngeal and parapharyngeal space extending into the left parotid gland, involving both the deep and superficial lobes.the fluid collection extends inferiorly medially along the mandible into the sublingual and bilateral submandibular spaces.the largest component within the left parapharyngeal and parotid space measures 2.9 x 3.3 x 3.4 cm.there is adjacent fatty stranding with obscuration of the parapharyngeal fat planes.also noted is mass effect on the airway within the oropharynx, with rightward shift.the inflammatory changes extends inferiorly to the level of the epiglottis with obliteration of the left vallecula and narrowing of the supraglottic airway.also noted is severe attenuation of the distal left internal jugular vein, which appears unopacified for several millimeters, possibly representing a short segment of thrombosis.the jugular vein reconstitutes at the level of the skull base and the sigmoid sinus.additionally, there is abrupt termination of several of the branches of the external jugular vein.the right internal jugular vein is patent.the cervical carotid arteries are patent with atherosclerotic calcification noted at the left carotid bulb.multiple prominent and borderline enlarged level 1b and 2a lymph nodes are identified bilaterally measuring up to 9 mm in short axis.evaluation of the madible demonstrates small periapical lucencies surrounding the right central and lateral incisors.an ng tube is noted within the oropharynx and esophagus.bilateral pleural effusions are noted at the lung apices.there is a 10 mm prevascular lymph node noted (2:98).multilevel degenerative changes noted throughout the cervical spine.the visualized brain parenchyma is unremarkable in appearance.
summary: extensive multiloculated rim-enhancing fluid collection with foci of gas extending inferiorly from the left parotid gland and parapharyngeal space into the sublingual and bilateral submandubular space.these findings are highly suspicious for abscess.inflammatory changes extend inferiorly to the level of the epiglottis with obliteration of the left vallecula and narrowing of the supraglottic airway.severe attenuation of the superior aspect of the jugular vein with several millimeters of non-enhancement suspicious for short segment thrombosis.reconstitution of the jugular vein noted at the jugular foramen/skull base.moderate bilateral pleural effusions.these findings were communicated to dr.___ as on ___ at 4:30 p.m.

text: there is a large mediastinal mass extending cranially through the thoracic inlet to the level of the thyroid gland.several pulmonary metastatic lesions are seen, better evaluated on the chest ct performed today.the mediastinal mass abuts and encases the origin of the aortic arch tributaries.the patient has a tracheostomy, and there is some mucus within the airways at the insertion site.no definite area of focal narrowing is seen.the cervical vessels appear patent.

text: subcutaneous gas is seen within the right neck.the gas extends down to the jugular sheath.bubbles of gas are seen immediately adjacent to the right jugular vein.there is normal opacification of the neck vessels.no abnormal fluid collections are identified.a left subclavian central venous line is seen with tip in the left mid- brachiocephalic vein.a nasogastric tube and endotracheal tube are visualized.the tip of the endotracheal tube is located at the thoracic inlet.there is a left-sided pneumothorax with collapse of the left upper lobe.on the inferior most image subcutaneous gas is seen extending through the left lateral chest wall.the osseous structures are unremarkable.mucosal thickening is present in the left maxillary sinus.there is fluid in the right maxillary sinus and in the ethmoid sinus.the visualized brain parenchyma is unremarkable.

text: the previously demonstrated left frontal hemorrhage is partially identified, there is mass effect along the frontal region towards the right and mild deviation of the vessels, including the anterior and middle cerebral arteries.the vascular structures demonstrate contrast enhancement in both anterior cerebral arteries and middle cerebral arteries, there is segmental narrowing of the left middle cerebral artery, likely reflecting atherosclerotic disease.there is also mild bilateral narrowing of both internal carotid arteries in the carotid siphons (400b:13), possibly related with atherosclerotic disease.the aortic arch demonstrate a punctate calcification adjacent to the origin of the left common carotid, the carotid bifurcations are patent with no evidence of stenosis.small punctate calcification is demonstrated at the right cervical carotid bifurcation (3:137).punctate calcification is visualized adjacent to the origin of the left vertebral artery with no evidence of stenosis and the right vertebral artery appears patent.unchanged bilateral mucosal thickening identified at the ethmoidal air cells, sphenoid sinus, and bilateral maxillary sinuses.stable and unchanged, previously described complex fractures in the skull base and cervical spine, please refer to the prior head ct report dated ___, for further details.

text: the right vertebral artery appears patent without dissection adjacent to the fracture.the left vertebral artery also appear patent without dissection or stenosis or occlusion.the right carotid artery is normal in appearance.the left carotid artery shows normal appearance in the lower cervical region.at the skull base, there is fracture involving to the carotid canal.a linear lucency seen in the upper left internal carotid artery appears to be artifactual as it is discontinuous.no definite extravasation is identified.minimal soft tissue swelling is seen near the upper cervical internal carotid artery, which could be due to adjacent soft tissue edema from fracture.
summary: no evidence of dissection of right vertebral artery near the fracture.fracture involving the carotid canal on the left side.although there does not appear to be any extravasation of contrast or definite dissection in the left internal carotid artery, the evaluation is somewhat limited as the artery is only partially included near the skull base on this neck cta study.if the patient's condition improves, a ct angiography of the head can help for further assessment.alternatively, mri and mra can be obtained for better assessment.comment 1.the ct angiography images through the thorax demonstrate thrombus at the main pulmonary artery bifurcation extending to both pulmonary arteries.this was further evaluated with ct angiography of the chest.2.csf intensities are seen extending to the right neural foramen and to the extraforaminal region on the right at c6-7 level.this could be due to a perineural cyst.however, if patient has right-sided weakness or signs of brachial plexus injury, mri can help for further assessment of this area.

text: comparison is made to an mr of the head from ___.
summary: severe atherosclerotic disease of the aortic arch with short segment occlusion of the proximal left subclavian artery with reconstitution via a left common carotid artery to subclavian artery bypass graft.moderate stenosis of the origin of the right vertebral artery.multisegmental stenoses of the right carotid artery including the distal cervical internal carotid artery, but without high-grade stenoses.no aneurysms or intracranial vessel occlusions.

text: bilateral lung apices demonstrate diffuse patchy areas of ground- glass opacity, mainly within the right anterior upper lobe.the amount of ground-glass opacification has significantly improved when compared with prior ct of the chest dated ___.no nodules or areas of focal consolidation are identified within the lung apices bilaterally.multiple prominent mediastinal lymph nodes are identified which do not meet ct criteria for pathologic enlargement.when compared with prior exam, the thyroid has undergone interval growth.this is best seen on series 2, image 34, where the thyroid measures 6.0 x 2.8 cm.in a similar section, on prior study, this measured 5.4 x 3.4 cm.the nasopharynx, soft tissues, and vasculature are normal in appearance.the imaged portions of the paranasal sinuses are clear.bone windows show degenerative changes, but no fractures, or lytic/sclerotic abnormalities.
summary: interval increase in thyroid gland.no lymphadenopathy within the neck.

text: there is no fluid collection or significant lymphadenopathy.major cervical vessels enhance normally.atherosclerotic calcifications are noted in the vertebral arteries.the airway is patent.the evaluation of oropharynx is somewhat limited by streaky artifact.mild fullness in the region of the right palatine tonsil could be positional.this area should be amenable to direct visualization.nasointestinal tube is in place.the evaluation of lung apices is limited by breathing motion artifact.the osseous structures demonstrate no destructive lesion.
summary: no abscess.somewhat limited evaluation of the oropharynx with apparent asymmetric fullness of the right palatine tonsil.the area is amenable to direct visualization.

text: there is a 15mm lymph node seen at the level 2 jugular chain on the left side.a 13mm lymph node is also present at the same level on the contralateral side.there are no other intra or extra nodal mass lesions present.there is no overt vascular abnormality present.there are no areas of pathologic enhancement.enlarged lymph nodes are also present in the a-p window and the mediastinum.the largest one measures 16mm.
summary: enlarged lymph nodes at the level 2 jugular chain on the right and left sides.mediastinal lymph adenopathy.there are no pathologically enlarged lymph nodes present in the submandibular area.

text: the study is compared with dedicated ct of the trachea with reconstructions, dated ___, as well as chest radiographs dating to ___.again demonstrated is the enormous multinodular thyroid goiter, which extends uninterrupted from the level of the left oropharynx to the level of the superior aortic arch.this contains numerous calcifications and several discrete nodules, many somewhat cystic.it markedly displaces the cervical trachea to the left and markedly compresses and effaces its right lateral wall.at the level of maximal compression at the thoracic inlet (roughly the level of the mid-clavicle) the trachea is slit-like and measures 20 mm (ap) by 4 mm (trv), (series 2, image 38); on a roughly comparable section on the ___ examination (series 2, image 21) it measured only approximately 2.5 mm in maximal transverse dimension.the region of maximal narrowing at the thoracic inlet traverses a roughly 4 cm segment of the upper thoracic trachea with more normal tracheal contour, caudal to the sternoclavicular articulation.there are numerous small lymph node in the anterior and posterior cervical triangles, bilaterally, not meeting size criteria for pathologic enlargement, unchanged.the limited included portions of the lung apices are clear.
summary: enormous multinodular goiter, extending from the level of the oropharynx to the aortic arch.there is marked associated tracheal deviation and compression, particularly at the level of the thoracic inlet, this is no worse than that demonstrated on the ___ study.no new site of tracheal compression is identified.

text: the nasopharynx and oropharynx are patent.no abnormal fluid collections are identified.the carotid arteries and jugular veins appear intact, although this is a somewhat limited evaluation due to the lack of intravenous contrast.the thyroid is symmetric.no significant lymphadenopathy is identified within the neck or mediastinum.limited views of the lung apices demonstrate no significant nodular densities or infiltrates.
summary: no evidence of abscess.

text: there is calcified atherosclerotic plaque involving both carotid bulbs and proximal icas.the right cervical internal carotid artery has minimum diameters of 6.0 mm, proximally, and 4.5 mm, distally.within the proximal right ica, at the site of greatest narrowing due to atherosclerotic disease, the dmin measures 3.5 mm.the left cervical internal carotid artery demonstrates minimum diameter of 4.0 mm, proximally, and 4.5 mm, distally.at the site of greatest atherosclerotic narrowing within the proximal left ica, the dmin measures 3 mm.there is no site of significant atherosclerotic disease seen more distally in either internal carotid artery.the origin of the left vertebral artery demonstrates significant circumferential plaque, with resultant high-grade stenosis; there is slight post-stenotic dilatation and resumption of caliber, distally.the origin of the right vertebral artery is widely patent.otherwise, there is no focal stenosis involving the vertebral arteries.there appears to be a right fetal pca intracranially, incompletely imaged.a fetal-equivalent left pca is also likely present.visualized lung apices demonstrate mild paraseptal emphysema.mild-to-moderate degenerative changes are noted within the cervical spine, worst at c5-6, incompletely assessed.
summary: calcified atherosclerotic disease within the carotid bulbs and proximal icas, bilaterally.however, there is no site of greater than 50% diameter stenosis.significant plaque at the origin of the left vertebral artery, with resultant high-grade stenosis.

text: as described on the head ct acquired ___, the soft tissue prominence adjacent to the right ramus of the mandible appears stable compared to ___.again noted are extensive post-surgical changes to the right mandible and maxilla.there is cortical irregularity of the right mandible and a fistula tract extending to the mandible.several small, non-pathologically enlarged lymph nodes are present in both jugulodigastric chains.the thyroid gland is not enlarged.the major vessels of the neck appear normal.the right apical opacity/consolidation appears stable.
summary: stable appearance of the prominent soft tissue adjacent to the right ramus of the mandible.fistula tract extending to the right ramus of the mandible.unchanged appearance of the right apical consolidation compared with chest ct ___.this could represent chronic collapse/scarring, possibly as the result of remote granulomatous infection.

text: there is a 44 x 20 mm left supraclavicular pouch containing mucous secretion that connects either to the distal portion of the post-cricoid pharynx or the proximal portion of the resected esophagus.scattered lymph nodes are noted at multiple levels within the neck and in the superior mediastinum which are not enlarged by ct size criteria.patient has a left ___ prosthesis adjacent to the thyroid cartilage.the visible vessels are patent.a hypodense nodule is noted measuring 9 mm in the right inferior thyroid lobe.the partially imaged brain is unremarkable.the visible paranasal sinuses and mastoid air cells are well aerated.the partially imaged lungs show right upper lobe tree-in-___ opacities.a right port-a-cath terminates in the distal svc appropriately.
summary: patient is status post esophagectomy with a spit fistula in the left supraclavicular region.left vocal cord ___ prosthesis.tree-in-___ opacities in the right upper lobe could be related to aspiration.scattered lymph nodes in the multiple levels in the neck and the superior mediastinum are not enlarged by ct size criteria.hypodense nodule in the right thyroid lobe inferiorly, may be evaluated with a dedicated ultrasound if one has recently not been performed.

text: calcification is seen throughout the aortic arch.normal contrast enhancement is seen within the right and left carotid arteries with no evidence of carotid artery dissection.no evidence of contrast extravasation is identified within the neck.there has been apparent surgery within the right side of the neck in the region of the right submandibular gland with evidence of stranding/residual scarring in this region.stranding of the soft tissues in the anterior neck is also seen consistent with soft tissue edema.an endotracheal tube and ng tube are present.there appears to be a compression deformity of the c7 vertebral body with a possible retropulse fragment within the spinal canal.degenerative changes are seen throughout the cervical spine.please refer to the ct of the cervical spine report for details.
summary: ct of the neck demonstrates no evidence of carotid artery dissection, hematoma, or contrast extravasation.there appears to have been prior surgery within the right side of the neck in the region of the submandibular gland.ct of the chest demonstrates a small residual left-sided pneumothorax and a tiny right pneumothorax.bilateral pulmonary contusions.there is also an element of chf.manubrial and numerous bilateral rib fractures.there is a hematoma anterior to the manubrium, and expansion of the left-sided lattismus/serratus anterior consistent with hematoma.subcutaneous air is also seen within the left lateral chest wall.hypodensity within the spleen with some high density fluid surrounding the spleen consistent with a splenic laceration.ascites throughout the abdomen.linear hypodensity in the liver may represent a normal variant, though laceration cannot be excluded.no hematoma is seen around the liver.compression deformities of the t4, t12, l4 and l5 vertebral bodies.copd.these findings were discussed with the surgical house staff caring for the patient.

text: there has been overall interval decrease in size of the ill-defined right laryngeal soft tissue density.the lesion involves the right true and false vocal cords, and it extends into the subglottis.extent into the contralateral vocal cord remains present, but is more difficult to delineate.the right arytenoid cartilage is sclerotic, unchanged.there is no evidence of lymphadenopathy.the salivary glands are unremarkable.the thyroid is enlarged and nodular, grossly similar to the previous study, but not optimally evaluated.a tracheostomy tube remains in place.again identified is a calcified granuloma measuring 5 mm in the imaged right upper lung.there is bilateral emphysema and pleural/parenchyma scarring in the imaged upper lungs, as before.there are mucus retention cysts in the maxillary sinuses, unchanged.there is opacification of multiple left mastoid air cells, new since the prior study.there are degenerative changes of the cervical spine without evidence of high- grade spinal canal narrowing.there is no evidence of lytic or blastic osseous lesions.
summary: decreased size of the right laryngeal soft tissue lesion.it is difficult to determine how much of the lesion constitutes residual tumor versus radiation-related change.contralateral extension probably remains present, but is more difficult to delineate.mri could be more helpful due to better soft tissue contrast.nodular and enlarged thyroid gland.recommend thyroid ultrasound for further evaluation, if not already performed elsewhere.

text: at the site of left orbital exenteration an flap reconstruction, numerous clips are seen.there is considerable soft tissue swelling with fluid seen immediately lateral to the nasal bone (series 2, image 44), adjacent to surgical clips, where a locule of gas is also seen (series 2, image 46) and posteriorly in the surgical site (series 2, image 47).a bony defect is seen in the lamina papyracea (series 2, image 45) and is age indeterminate in the absence of comparison films.no intracranial abscess is seen.no definable abscess is seen at the operative site.there is apparent extension of soft tissue density into the left ethmoidal sinuses.there is also mucosal thickening in the left maxillary sinus.the vessels appear to be patent with no evidence of thrombosis.the thyroid is enlarged and heterogeneously enhancing.the lung apices appear normal.
summary: swollen soft tissue at the site of orbital exenteration and flap repair with fluid collections at numerous sites and a locule of gas near surgical material.there is apparent extension into the left ethmoid sinus, where there is a defect in the lamina papyracea of unknown chronicity.no definable abscess.comment:these results were discussed with dr.___ ___ by dr.___ ___ at 2:30 a.m.___.

text: there has been interval placement of a drainage catheter with tip terminating at approximately the c2 level.the prevertebral hematoma has markedly decreased in size from ___ and ___.an endotracheal tube, ng tube, and a left central line are partially visualized.small locules of air within the subcutaneous tissues of the right neck is likely related to the placement of the drainage catheter.bilateral maxillary sinus opacification is partially visualized, better assessed on ct of the head ___, ___.visualized lungs reveal a moderate right pleural effusion.
summary: interval marked decrease in size of the prevertebral hematoma, following placement of drainage catheter.right pleural effusion.

text: previously detailed t-spine fracture is better visualized on the recent ct torso as are numerous thoracic abnormalities related to the trauma.otherwise, there is no fracture through the cervical spine.incidental note is made of moderate amount of mediastinal gas, unchanged from the previous ct and concerning for hollow viscus injury.cta images show the carotid and vertebral arteries as well as their major branches to be patent bilaterally with no evidence of aneurysm or traumatic injury.there is no evidence of extravasation on delayed images.the left vertebral artery is hypoplastic along its length.there is no evidence of aneurysm formation.
summary: numerous post-traumatic sequelae which are better characterized on a previous ct scan done hours earlier.however, angiographic images show no vascular sequela of trauma in the head or neck.

text: there is swelling of the oropharyngeal soft tissues, the tonsillar pillars and the base of the tongue, causing narrowing of the oropharynx.there is also asymmetry and fullness in the region of the piriform sinuses, as well as valleculae.this needs evaluation with direct ent examination.there is also swelling of the soft tissues of the hypophararynx and adjacent portions of the esophagus, not adequately assessed on the present study.in addition, there is increased attenuation of the fat in the right side of the neck, predominantly in the carotid space, with some heterogeneous and hypodense appearance.there is indentation on the right internal jugular vein by the area of increased attenuation.this is also seen extending down, along the common carotid artery, into the region of the thoracic inlet, (series 2, image 15).there is also some increased attenuation of the fat in the lateral soft tissues of the neck posterior to the sternocleidomastoid.no definite ring-enhancing lesions are noted to suggest well formed abscess.clips are noted in the region of the thyroid on both sides.multilevel degenerative changes are noted in the cervical spine.however, the cervical spine is not adequately assessed on the present study.the level of spine surgery is not clear from the present study.some scant atherosclerotic vascular calcifications are noted in the aortic arch, and in the common carotid arteries.multiple small lymph nodes are noted in both sides of the neck, some of which are mildly enlarged.
summary: significant swelling/inflammation of the soft tissues at the base of tongue, oropharynx, with fullness in the vallecula and the piriform sinuses, overall resulting in moderate to marked narrowing of the oropharynx.the etiology of this finding is uncertain from the present study.to correlate with direct ent examination.fullness of the hypopharynx and adjacent portions of esophagus - no adequately assessed on the present study- further evaluation recommended.increased attenuation of the fat in the carotid space, with soft tissue attenuation opacity, with heterogeneous appearance, causing indentation on the right internal jugular vein extending down along the carotid space, into the region of the thoracic inlet.this may relate to inflammation, phlegmon, and radiation-related changes if there is history of radiation in the past and less likely neoplastic.close followup evaluation, with ultrasound can be considered to evaluate for any abscess, given the patient's symptoms of fever.findings and recommendations were discussed with dr.___ by dr.___ on ___.

text: no carotid or vertebral artery dissection is detected.the distal cervical internal carotid artery measures 3.3 mm on the right and 4.6 mm on the left.mild calcified plaque is demonstrated at the right carotid artery bifurcation, without hemodynamically significant stenosis.two areas of relative narrowing in the mid cervical portion of the left internal carotid artery with minimal diameter of 2.8 mm (series 3: image 232), most suggestive of athlerosclerotic changes.calcified atherosclerotic plaque is present at the origins of the vertebral arteries (bilaterally) without hemodynamically significant stenosis.post-traumatic changes within the chest include large left pneumothorax, atelectasis, multiple rib fractures, and subcutaneous left chest wall emphysema is better evaluated on dedicated ct torso.cervical spine fractures are also better evaluated on prior ct cervical spine.secretions are present within the distal trachea distal to the endotracheal tube cuff.
summary: no evidence of traumatic vascular injury to the circle of ___ or neck vessels.atherosclerotic changes with calcified atherosclerotic plaque at the origins of the bilateral vertebral arteries, left carotid bifurcation, and two regions of narrowing in the mid cervical portion of the left internal carotid arteries without hemodynamically significant stenoses.traumatic injuries including rib fractures, cervical spine fractures, subdural and subarachnoid hemorrhages are better evaluated on prior dedicated cross- sectional imaging.

text: extensive osseous findings of multiple myeloma are seen, with innumerable tiny punched out lytic lesions seen throughout the cervical spine as well as the skull base, the vast majority tiny in size, with a few slightly larger foci only measuring up to 6 mm (2:12 in the left sphenoid).no soft tissue mass is seen in the neck to explain hoarse voice.the study is somewhat limited due to lack of intravenous contrast.there is no prevertebral soft tissue swelling or thickening.the visualized paranasal sinuses appear unremarkable except for minimal left maxillary sinus mucosal thickening (2:22).there is partial pneumatization of the optic strut on the right.there is no cervical lymphadenopathy.the mastoid air cells and middle ear cavities appear clear.the cervical spine demonstrates normal alignment.however, a disc osteophyte complex is seen at the c5-c6 level causing canal narrowing and putting mass effect on the cord (6:29).the lung apices again demonstrate interstitial septal thickening better evaluated on ct torso ___, possibly related to infection and/or known heart failure.
summary: numerous osseous findings of multiple myeloma include innumerable tiny lytic lesions throughout the cervical spine, which gives the bones a somewhat mottled appearance.no evidence of focal plasmacytoma or other soft tissue mass within the limits of non-contrast examination.disc osteophyte complex at the c5-c6 level causes canal narrowing/mass effect on the cord.results relayed to dr.___ ___ 6p ___.

text: there are no prior images available for comparison.if prior images are available, they could be digitized so we could make an adequate comparison.in the left side of the neck, there is a 9 x 7 mm small nodule or slightly enlarged lymph node adjacent to the lateral aspect of the hyoid bone.there is a prominent and slightly irregular thyroid gland with areas of low density, particularly in the right lobe.this may be the result of a multinodular goiter and an ultrasound is advised for better characterization.there are mulitple small suboccipital lymph nodes.
summary: small left nodule or slightly enlarged lymph node at lateral to the hyoid bone without prior study for comparison.prominent thyroid gland, which may be secondary to multinodular goiter.

text: the carotid and vertebral arteries and their major branches are patent.abrupt change in direction at the origin of the left vertebral artery limits evaluation for stenosis; mild stenosis cannot be excluded.there is no evidence for aneurysm formation or other vascular abnormality.the penetrating branches of the basilar artery are below the resolution of this study; no basilar artery atheroma is seen.note is made of fenestration of the proximal basilar artery.minimal plaque is noted in the right subclavian artery.the visualized portions of the lungs demonstrate increased confluence of bilateral diffuse opacities.
summary: fenestration of the proximal basilar artery without occlusion or atheroma; mild stenosis at the origin of the left vertebral artery cannot be excluded.increased confluence of bilateral lung opacities, concerning for worsening infectious process.preliminary findings were reported by wet read.

text: the bilateral vertebral and carotid arteries are patent.the right vertebral artery is diminutive in comparison to the left vertebral artery.there is a slight fusiform dilatation of the distal right vertebral artery as it courses over the posterior arch of c1 measuring approximately 3 mm in diameter.there are otherwise no changes in caliber of the vertebral or carotid arteries or luminal irregularities.the visualized intracranial vessels are unremarkable with no evidence of aneurysm.the visualized intracranial contents including previously reported areas of hemorrhage are unchanged from the concurrent ct of the head.incidental note is made of metallic fixation hardware involving the mandible.there is slightly limited assessment of the arch vessels at the level of the thoracic inlet due to streak artifact from adjacent dense venous contrast.the visualized lung apices are unremarkable.the visualized nasopharynx, oropharynx and hypopharynx are unremarkable.no enhancing mass lesions are demonstrated within the neck.
summary: mild ectasia of the distal right and diminutive vertebral artery as it courses over the posterior arch of c1.this finding is of uncertain significance, possibly relating to a branch vessel dislocation though one is not identified.there is no other evidence to support this indication.

text: the mixed-attenuating lesion with central hypoattenuating region, measuring 3.8 x 2.9 cm seen in the right posterior oropharynx, centered in the tonsillar region, has decreased in size since the prior study.the craniocaudal margins are indistinct.there is diffuse soft tissue swelling noted in the right > left side of nasopharynx, oropharynx including the epiglottis,right pyriform sinus and the hypopharynx, which could be related to the recent radiotherapy which limits evaluation of any underlying mass .the fat plane separating the mass lesion and the right mandible is not well delineated in the current study, but was seen in the prior study.this could be related to post radiation changes or extension of the mass lesion.there is significant narrowing of the hypopharynx due to the soft tissue swelling noted at that level.previously visualized multiple enlarged right sided lymph nodes, are not seen in the current study.the level ii lymph node seen in the left side is slightly smaller in size compared to the prior study, now measuring 6 mm in the short axis and previously measured 8 mm.the parotid glands and submandibular glands appear unremarkable.airway appears patent but significantly narrowed at level of the hypopharynx.great vessels of the neck and the aortic arch show atheromatous calcification.thyroid gland appears unremarkable.again noted are diffuse emphysematous changes in the lung apices.diffuse cervical spine degenerative changes noted.no lytic or sclerotic lesions detected.
summary: interval decrease in size of the mass lesion with features suggesting necrosis, in the right posterolateral oropharynx and hypopharynx.non visualized ipsilateral lymphnodes with decrease in size of the left level ii node.2.diffuse soft tissue swelling involving the right > left sides of nasopharynx, right posterior oropharynx, and the proximal hypopharynx with significant narrowing of the hpopharynx.fat plane between the right side of mandible and the lesion not clearly visualized.these findings could represent post radiation changes or a recurrent lesion.an mri is recommended for better differentiation of the above.stable moderate centrilobular emphysema in the lung apices.

text: the carotid and vertebral arteries and their major branches within the neck are patent without evidence of stenosis.there is no evidence of aneurysm formation, arterial dissection, or other vascular abnormality.the right internal carotid artery is patent without hemodynamically significant stenosis.the cervical portion of the right internal carotid artery measures 5.5 mm in diameter.the left internal carotid artery is patent without evident stenosis.the cervical portion of the left internal carotid measures 5.8 mm in diameter.the internal carotid arteries are medialized bilaterally.the fracture/subluxation of c6-c7 is again seen and extends from the vertebral body through the posterior elements and articular processes.
summary: the vertebral arteries are patent without evidence of stenosis, aneurysm formation, dissection, or other vascular abnormality.the carotid arteries are patent without evidence of stenosis.the fracture/subluxation of c6-c7 is again seen.

text: there is a large rim-enhancing multiloculated fluid collection predominantly centered within the left parapharyngeal space extending into the retropharyngeal space and the carotid space.the collection measures 7.0 x 4.2 x 3.2 cm.there is significant mass effect on the airway.there is anterior displacement and mild mass effect on the left common carotid artery.there is mild narrowing of the left common carotid artery seen in images 55, 54 in series 2, raising concern for spasm of the left common carotid artery.there is significant mass effect on the left internal jugular vein causing narrowing of the vein, without definite occlusion at this time.there is minimal fat stranding just above the level of the thoracic inlet, but no definite mediastinal extension is seen at this time.the patient is status post extraction of a left mandibular wisdom tooth.no osseous findings are seen to suggest an osteomyelitis.extensive bilateral reactive cervical lymphadenopathy is seen involving the anterior and the posterior cervical nodal groups, left greater than right.the imaged portion of the brain is unremarkable.
summary: large abscess centered in the left parapharyngeal space, extending to the retropharyngeal and left carotid space.mass effect and narrowing of the oropharyngeal airway.mild mass effect and possible mild narrowing of the left common carotid artery, is concerning for developing vasospasm.significant mass effect on the left internal jugular vein, without complete occlusion at this time.no mediastinal extension of the abscess.extensive reactive cervical lymphadenopathy.no evidence of osteomyelitis of the mandible.the findings were discussed with dr.___ immediately after the study.

text: there is dissection identified in the thoracic aorta.the dissection extends to the left subclavian artery as well as to the innominate artery.the evaluation of the origin of the right common carotid from the innominate artery is limited due to artifacts.however, there is no definite extension of the dissection seen in either of the common carotid arteries.the internal carotid arteries appear patent.the vertebral arteries also appear normal in appearance.
summary: aortic dissection is seen to be extending to the left subclavian artery and the innominate artery.no extension to the carotids is identified, although evaluation of the carotids near the thoracic inlet is somewhat limited due to artifacts.

text: no acute fracture or malalignment is seen in the cervical spine.a known left-sided skull fracture is partially imaged.within the cervical spine, the atlantoaxial and atlanto-occipital articulations are preserved.the prevertebral soft tissues are grossly symmetric and unremarkable.the neck vessels enhance symmetrically without evidence of dissection or significant stenosis.the visualized paranasal sinuses and mastoid air cells are clear.the included portions of the lung apices are grossly unremarkable.
summary: no acute cervical spine fracture or malalignment.patent major arteries of neck.

text: the common carotid, proximal internal carotid, and proximal external carotid arteries are opacified bilaterally.the vertebral arteries are also opacified bilaterally.there is extensive calcification at both carotid bifurcations extending into the carotid bulbs.there is associated stenosis at the carotid bulbs bilaterally, but its severity cannot be assessed due to the calcifications.calcifications are also present at the origin of the left external carotid artery, limiting the evaluation for any possible stenosis.there are calcifications and stenosis at the origin of the left subclavian artery from the aortic arch.the severity of the stenosis cannot be adequately assessed.there is a moderate stenosis at the left vertebral artery origin from the subclavian artery.the visualized nonvascular soft tissues appear unremarkable.degenerative changes are noted in the cervical spine facet joints at multiple levels.
summary: extensive calcifications at the carotid bifurcations bilaterally, which limits the assessment of degree of stenosis.calcifications at the left external carotid artery origin, limiting the evaluation for presence of stenosis.calcifications and stenosis of the left subclavian artery origin.moderate stenosis of the left vertebral artery origin.

text: the patient is status post transdural resection of the lateral oropharyngeal wall tumor, mandibulotomy and mandibular plating.surgical clips in the left tonsillar area with associated fat density material are similar to the prior study.multiple locules of gas in the subcutaneous fat extending deeper into the soft tissues lateral to the surgical clips have increased in size and number from the previous study.no focal or drainable collections are identified.soft tissue density overall has increased and there is increased leftward deviation of the supraglottic airway.the infraglottic airway appears slightly narrow in comparison to the prior study.the tracheostomy tube is unchanged in position.the left internal jugular vein remains compressed, similar to the prior study.the lung apices are clear.there are no concerning osseous lesions.
summary: increased soft tissue density and gas in the left neck in the areas of prior surgery, without focal collection.this may represent infection in the appropriate setting and/or a fistula.increased leftward deviation of the supraglottic airway and probable narrowing of the infraglottic airway above the tracheostomy.final attending comment: there are some areas of low density in the left neck( image 24-26) which may represent early abscess or phlegmon communicating with the skin which may correlate with clinically known spontaneously draining abscess.there is moderate edema in the retropharyngeal space and effacement of the left internal jugular vein.

text: in the region of the right palatine tonsil (4:7) is a poorly defined lesion.(2/36) this lesion in the right palatine tonsil appears to extend posteriorly, however, the parapharyngeal fat in this region is normal.there are scattered nodes, none of which meet ct criteria for pathologic enlargement.the borders of this lesion and the degree of enhancement is difficult to assess, given the lack of precontrast iamges.there are no additional lesions identified.bilateral parotid gland and bilateral submandibular glands appear normal.the carotid and vertebral arteries appear normal without significant calcification or stenosis.both lobes of the thyroid appear unremarkable.the partially visualized lung apices are clear.osseous structures appear intact.there is minimal mucosal thickening of the maxillary sinuses.paranasal sinuses, mastoid and ethmoid air cells are otherwise clear.
summary: right palatine tonsil lesion incompletely assessed on this study as the degree of extension and enhancement is difficult to assess.the parapharyngeal fat in the region however, is normal and there are no abnormally enlarged lymph nodes.would recommend mri of the neck without and with contrast for further evaluation and characterization.

text: there is complete occlusion of the right internal carotid artery at its origin.the right internal carotid artery reconstitutes at its supraclinoid portion, likely from the ophthalmic artery.there are extensive calcifications of the left internal carotid artery from its petrous portions through to the supraclinoid portions with associated areas of stenosis.a large calcification is also seen at the origin of the right vertebral artery with an associated moderate degree of stenosis.the left vertebral artery is patent and dominant.the major tributaries of the circle of ___ are patent including the right middle cerebral artery.a large right middle cerebral artery territorial infarction is again seen.there is no evidence of hydrocephalus or shift of normally midline structures.osseous structures are remarkable for moderate degenerative changes of the cervical spine.surrounding soft tissues are unremarkable.
summary: occlusion of the right internal carotid artery at its origin.the vessel reconstitutes at its supraclinoid portion likely via the ophthalmic artery.extensive calcifications of the left internal carotid artery extending from the petrous to the supraclinoid portions with likely associated moderate degrees of stenosis.calcification and moderate stenosis of the origin of the right vertebral artery.patent circle of ___ including the right middle cerebral artery and branches in the region of the previously identified right frontal and parietal lobe infarcts.

text: there is slight asymmetric prominence of the left pharyngeal tonsil in comparison with the right.this measures 1.6 x 1.6 cm.the adjacent retropharyngeal fat planes are preserved and there is no evidence of central hypodensity to suggest necrosis or abscess.there is no retropharyngeal fluid collection identified.small submental lymph nodes are seen.there are additional subcentimeter bilateral anterior and posterior cervical triangle nodes which do not meet criteria for pathologic enlargement.on the right, an 8-mm anterior triangle node is seen.the airway appears patent.the carotid arteries and jugular veins are patent bilaterally.no pathologically enlarged nodes are visualized in the imaged portion of the superior mediastinum.the visualized portion of the lung apices appears unremarkable.the thyroid gland appears within normal limits.the mastoid air cells and visualized portions of the paranasal sinuses are normally pneumatized, with the exception of questionable rounded soft tissue density within the right maxillary sinus which may represent mucus retention cyst versus polyp.the visualized osseous structures demonstrate no evidence of suspicious lytic or sclerotic osseous lesions.
summary: asymmetric prominence of the left pharyngeal tonsil measuring 1.6 cm in diameter without evidence of abscess or retropharyngeal fluid collection.probable mucous retention cyst versus polyp in the right maxillary sinus.

text: no hemorrhage, mass lesion, hydrocephalus or evidence of infarction noted intracranially.again identified are the fractures of the anterior and posterior arches of c1 as described on previous study.the left vertebral artery is normal in appearance.previously normal caliber right vertebral artery is now narrowed along its course and is lost to visualization in the segment from c2 to the foramina magna.the internal carotid arteries appear normal in caliber and contour throughout their course.no pathologic cervical lymphadenopathy is identified.incompletely visualized lung apices are normal in appearance.
summary: the previously normal caliber of right vertebral artery is now significantly narrowed throughout its visualized course.the segment from c2 to the foramen magna is not visualized which may represent either complete occlusion or a very small caliber patent region, too small to visualize on this resolution.these changes are all believed to be consequence of prior vertebral dissection.no area of infarction within this vascular distribution is identified.

text: the images demonstrate a prominent eccentric stenosis at the origin of the right internal carotid artery, with restoration of the lumen distally.on the left side, there is a tiny calcified plaque at the bifurcation of the left common carotid artery, without evidence of significant stenosis.minimal atherosclerotic changes involving the aortic arch without evidence of aneurysm in the visualzed portion is also noted.there is no evidence of lymphadenopathy, abscess, or fluid collections within the neck.the visualized brain parenchyma is unremarkable.the visualized paranasal sinuses are unremarkable.images of the lung apices demonstrate bilateral emphysematous changes, and peripheral ground-glass opacities that could be related to smoking.these ground-glass opacities can also represent infectious process in the appropriate clinical setting.please correlate clinically.in addition, two small solid nodules are seen in the right apex, with peripheral ill-defined opacities.

text: an endotracheal tube is positioned which deviates the tongue to the right side.the endotracheal tube extends to the upper thoracic region and the tip is above the level of carina.there is no evidence of soft tissue swelling seen in the submental region and no evidence of edema identified in the hypopharynx or in the laryngeal region.however, presence of endotracheal tube limits evaluation for asymmetry of these structures.there is an internal jugular vein catheter identified extending from the right side through the sternocleidomastoid muscle.there is some soft tissue stranding seen in the region but there is no evidence of a large hematoma or evidence of significant asymmetry of the sternocleidomastoid muscles.at the lung apex no obvious abnormalities are seen.vascular calcifications are noted.extensive opacification of paranasal sinuses are seen.there is high-density material in the left maxillary sinus which could be related to inspissated secretions but clinical correlation is recommended to exclude fungal infection.

text: there is a large, heterogeneous, ill-defined enhancing mass in the left neck measuring 5.7 (anteroposterior) x 5.4 (transverse) x 7.9 (craniocaudal) cm.this mass contains central hypodense areas, likely representative of necrosis, which appear to extend to the skin surface.this mass involves the left carotid, parapharyngeal, masticator, and parotid spaces.there is mass effect and rightward deviation of the airway which is otherwise patent.the mass compresses and occludes the left internal jugular vein.there is also occlusion of the distal branches of the left external carotid artery.the left internal carotid artery appears encased and markedly attenuated by the mass but not completely occluded.there is no evidence of bony destruction.multiple enhancing and prominent left submental (2:47) and supraclavicular (2:55) lymph nodes are visualized.a small amount of fluid is visualized in the piriform sinus, though the tumor does not appear to invade the hypopharynx.biapical scarring is visualized in the upper lobe.there is a 1.2 x 0.9 cm right thyroid hypodense nodule.
summary: heterogeneous ill-defined large left neck mass with internal necrosis compatible with a neoplasm.this mass encases and markedly attenuates the left internal carotid artery as well as occludes the distal branches of the left external carotid artery as well as the left internal jugular vein.please note that superimposed infection of this necrotic mass cannot be excluded on this imaging study.multiple enhancing left submental and submandibular lymph nodes suspicious for malignancy.right thyroid nodule.correlation with non-emergent ultrasound is recommended.biapical lung scarring.

text: the patient is status post thyroidectomy with numerous clips in the thyroid bed.no lymphadenopathy or neck mass is identified.calcifications of the right carotid artery are observed.soft tissue fullness in the superior mediastinum and hazy opacification of both lung apices is seen and better evaluated on the chest ct of the same day.the patient is status post lower cervical laminectomies.an irregular low attenuation collection is identified at the laminectomy site and may represent postoperative changes.osseous structures are stable.

text: there is no significant cervical lymphadenopathy or evidence of soft tissue or retropharyngeal abscess.there is mild thickening of the retropharyngeal/prevertebral soft tissues, consistent with inflammatory changes.there are bilateral pleural effusions, right greater than left, probably small-to-moderate in size.they are difficult to assess in these limited views of the lung apices.no other soft tissue or osseous abnormalities are noted.

text: there is complete resolution of soft tissue swelling/stranding in the right neck, representing interval resolution of the right neck infection.however, there is now significantly increased lymphadenopathy in the bilateral jugular chains and left supraclavicular region.a representative left supraclavicular node measures 15 x 8 mm (image 2:54), and large lymphoid jugular conglomerates measure 3.0 x 1.2 x 4.4 cm on the right (ap x trv x cc) and 2.7 x 1.3 x 4.8 cm on the left (ap x trv x cc), new from prior.given the patient has history of lymphoma, the findings are most concerning for recurrence/worsening of lymphoma.a small superimposed component of reactive lymphadenopathy cannot be excluded.the thyroid enhances symmetrically.the thrombosed right internal jugular vein is unchanged (image 2:47).the visualized lung apices are unremarkable.the central tracheobronchial tree is patent.the visualized great mediastinal vessels are normal.a small triangular anterior mediastinum anterior could represent either residual thymus or post-treatment thymic rebound.a small prevascular lymph node is not pathologically enlarged, measuring 7 mm in short axis(image 2:94).mild mucosal thickening is noted at the visualized maxillary sinuses.
summary: interval resolution of right neck infection.interval significant increase of lymphadenopathy along the bilateral jugular chains and left supraclavicular region, concerning for recurrence/worsening of lymphoma.a small superimposed component of reactive lymphadenopathy cannot be excluded.

text: no prior neck cts are available for comparison.within the left submandibular gland, there are two hyperdensities, with the largest measuring 6 x 4 mm.within the left side of the floor of the mouth, there are two hyperdense lesions, the largest of which is located anteriorly and measures approximately 9 x 7 mm.these findings likely represent stones within the submandibular gland and duct.no abnormal fluid collectons or other inflammatory changes are seen.atherosclerotic alcifications of the great vessels arising from the aortic arch and the carotid artery bifurcations bilaterally are seen.the left internal carotid artery is tortuous and swings medially immediately posterior to the mucosa of the hypopharynx and oropharynx.there is no evidence of cervical adenopathy.the thyroid gland is substernal in location.there are sternotomy wires as well as degenerative changes of the visualized cervical spine.
